<p>Gig workers&nbsp;: workers outside the traditional employer-employee relationship.</p>
<p>Platform workers : are those who access organisations or individuals through an online platform and provide services or solve specific problems.</p>
<h3>Issues&nbsp;</h3>
<ol>
<li><a href="https://www.drishtiias.com/daily-updates/daily-news-editorials/security-in-gig-economy"><span style="color:#e67e22">BENEFITS but not rights</span></a><span style="color:#e67e22">.&nbsp;</span></li>
<li>&nbsp;</li></ol>
<h3>Code on social security (CoSS),2020&nbsp;</h3>
<ol>
<li>NSSB</li>
<li>for ALL establishment&nbsp;</li>
<li>expand def of 'employee' (+contract workers) , 'inter state migrant' (+self employer from other state) , 'platform' (+more categories)</li></ol>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<h3>ISSUES with CoSS, 2020</h3>
<ol>
<li>UNIVERSAL SS? (&gt;10 employee)&nbsp;</li>
<li>fragmented setup for social services delivery not addressed</li>
<li>no clear def b/w platoform and gig</li>
<li>benefits are guaranteed? = NO&nbsp;</li>
<li>NO fixed responsibilty =&gt; do JOINT accountability&nbsp;</li></ol>
